      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "### Request audit contract\nEvery accepted `litellm_request` span becomes one log line in the Loki stream `{service_name=\"aigw-requests\"}`. Each line carries `aigw.user.id` (stable key subject), `aigw.user.name` (server-selected attribution only), `aigw.user.name_source`, `aigw.project.id`, `aigw.api_key.id` (SHA-256 fingerprint only), `aigw.request.id`, the model/token/cost fields, and approved prompt/completion content. Name sources are `portal_key_metadata`, `open_webui_signed_oidc`, or `key_subject`. Caller body values, plain user headers, end-user fields, and key aliases are never name authority. An unresolved name is dropped. `| logfmt` exposes fields with names such as `aigw_user_id`. `aigw_user_name` and `aigw_project_id` are also Loki stream labels, so the User and Project lists filter every panel. Raw authorization, API keys, JWTs, request headers, end-user fields, email, IP, and LiteLLM authentication metadata are removed before export. The readable name helps attribution; it never grants access. Prompt content is sensitive, so this dashboard is ADM-only.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.5",
      "title": "How to inspect a request",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "loki"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never"
          },
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "calcs": [
            "sum"
          ],
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom",
          "showLegend": true
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "desc"
        }
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.5",
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "loki"
          },
          "expr": "sum by (aigw_user_name) (count_over_time({service_name=\"aigw-requests\", aigw_user_name=~\"$user\", aigw_project_id=~\"$project\"} | logfmt [$__auto]))",
          "queryType": "range",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Requests by User",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
